until all this is cleared up.

134
00:09:45,618 --> 00:09:48,314
How much did they tell you
about what I do here at the school?

135
00:09:51,724 --> 00:09:53,817
Not much. You're some sort
of guidance counselor, right?

136
00:09:53,993 --> 00:09:59,124
Something like that. It's more
like a therapist, I guess you could say.

137
00:09:59,765 --> 00:10:03,132
I work with the students here
using my ability.

138
00:10:03,302 --> 00:10:05,099
All the kids here are 4400s,

139
00:10:05,271 --> 00:10:08,763
which means you missed years
of your family's lives.

140
00:10:09,241 --> 00:10:11,801
Your parents had another child
while you were gone.

141
00:10:11,978 --> 00:10:13,843
- Your brother, Curtis?
- Yeah.

142
00:10:14,013 --> 00:10:16,504
Before they got divorced.
I barely know him.

143
00:10:16,682 --> 00:10:17,944
That's where I come in.

144
00:10:20,319 --> 00:10:22,014
It's hard to explain, but if you let me,

145
00:10:22,188 --> 00:10:24,884
I can take you back to the years
when you were gone.

146
00:10:25,057 --> 00:10:28,220
You can meet your brother
when he was baby, see him grow up,

147
00:10:28,394 --> 00:10:30,294
and spend all the time
you need with him,

148
00:10:30,463 --> 00:10:32,397
and build the relationship
you don't have.

149
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:36,158
I'm sorry. What?
You wanna take me back in time?

150
00:10:36,335 --> 00:10:42,001
No. We'll be going to a world
we create using both our minds.

151
00:10:42,174 --> 00:10:44,665
And it will seem just as real
as this one.

152
00:10:50,950 --> 00:10:53,817
Look, no offense,

153
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:56,681
but maybe you should worry
about helping yourself.

154
00:10:58,090 --> 00:10:59,489
You think I need help?

155
00:11:01,127 --> 00:11:03,994
You have this sadness inside you.

156
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:06,859
Not sadness exactly.

157
00:11:07,033 --> 00:11:08,591
I guess rage would be the best word.

158
00:11:09,502 --> 00:11:12,062
It's because of what happened
to your husband and son

159
00:11:12,238 --> 00:11:14,229
all those years ago.

160
00:11:15,808 --> 00:11:17,867
You know about Billy and Paul?

161
00:11:18,044 --> 00:11:20,478
They got killed in a hit-and-run.

162
00:11:20,913 --> 00:11:22,403
The police never caught the guy.

163
00:11:25,751 --> 00:11:27,742
You try to move on...

164
00:11:28,921 --> 00:11:32,049
...and I guess you kind of have.

165
00:11:33,092 --> 00:11:36,289
But you still think about it every day.

166
00:11:36,996 --> 00:11:40,022
And there's still that rage.

167
00:11:43,703 --> 00:11:46,069
How do you know all that?

168
00:11:47,039 --> 00:11:51,408
You have an ability,
and I have an ability.

169
00:11:55,147 --> 00:12:00,175
Look, I'm sorry.
I'm just not up for this.

170
00:12:00,653 --> 00:12:04,919
